Summary

context-and-boundary hardening day

Today was mostly about making Codexify more explicit about what it is allowed to ingest, carry forward, and execute. The center of gravity was the new obsidian context request-plan path: the backend now consumes structured context directives instead of treating them as loose prompt-time hints, and that plumbing is covered by focused tests across the broker, resolver, chat completion service, and protocol token surface.

